# Branch-first workflow

## Always use a branch

- **Never** commit feature, fix, docs, or CI changes directly to `main`.
- Create a branch before editing: `git checkout -b feat/short-description` or
  `fix/...`, `chore/...`, `docs/...`.
- Open a PR after local CI passes; **the user merges** — see `no-auto-merge.mdc`.
- **Exception:** the user explicitly asks to commit/push to `main`.

## Before commit (mandatory)

Run the full CI mirror **before every commit** — same gates as GitHub
``lint-and-test``:

```bash
./scripts/ci-local.sh
```

Do not commit until it exits 0. See ``.cursor/rules/ci-before-commit.mdc``.

Optional extras (not substitutes): ``./scripts/ci-local.sh --integration``,
``--docs``, ``--helm``; ``./scripts/capability-test-suite.sh quick``.

``pre-commit install`` runs ``ci-local.sh`` on commit when ``src/``,
``tests/``, or ``scripts/`` change (and again on pre-push as a safety net).

## Before push

```bash
git push -u origin HEAD
gh pr create   # when the user asks for a PR — then STOP; do not merge
```

## Release tags

Version bumps and `v*` tags stay on `main` after merge, not on long-lived feature
branches. Tag only when the user requests a release.
